text: Walter Handschuhmacher (20 March 1904 - 30 April 1987) was a German swimmer. He competed in two events at the 1928 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1904 births Category:1987 deaths Category:German male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Germany Category:Swimmers at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Dortmund
